We are currently seeking for passionate and dynamic guest focused Recreation professionals who have the ability to deliver exceptional levels of customer service.Responsibilities:• To report for duty punctually wearing the correct uniform and name tag at all times.• To maintain the pool area in a tidy and clean manner at all times.• To be present around the pool at all times, to ensure the safety and meet the needs of guests and members.• To check the chemical balance of pools every hour and inform the Engineering department of any chemical imbalance, or any defects in the pool area.• To be responsible for the issue and return of all pool towels.• To ensure that there is always a sufficient stock of pool towels. • To collect soiled towels and arrange for their cleaning with the Laundry department.• To maintain good working relationships with your own colleagues and all other departments.• To have a complete understanding of and adhere to the hotel's policies relating to fire, hygiene, health and safety.• To maintain a high standard of personal appearance and hygiene at all times.• To respond to any changes as dictated by the industry, company or hotel. Qualifications & Experiences:Successful candidates should ideally have at least 1 year experience as a lifeguard.Should have lifeguard license (U.A.E certified). Good command of English, Arabic would be an advantage.
